Killer Tip: Abolish Video Mishaps

Problem: You're unable to run Windows after installing a new video
driver.

Solution: Before starting Windows, switch back to your old driver. Change
to the directory containing Windows--usually C:\WINDOWS and type SETUP.
Note: If you type SETUP from any other directory, Windows tries to
reinstall itself.

When Setup displays your current settings, press the up arrow until

you've selected Display. Press the Enter key to see a list of video
drivers, and then highlight your most recent driver (or VGA, if
necessary). Press Enter twice to make the driver you've selected active.
If Setup asks whether you want to use new drivers or current drivers,
choose Current. Once Setup has finished, you should be able to run
Windows again. This process works for other Setup problems, too.

